<body>
  <h1>Keith R Abrams</h1>
<p>Biostatistician - Health Technology Assessment (HTA) & Health Data Science</p>

<h2>Bio</h2>
I am Professor of Statistics & Data Science in the Department of Statistics and Adjunct Professor of 
Biostatistics in Warwick Medical School (WMS) at the University of Warwick, and am a NIHR Senior 
Investigator Emeritus as well as being Honorary Professor in the Centre for Health Economics at the 
University of York. Prior to this I held academic positions at the University of Leicester, 
the London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine (LSHTM) and King's College School of Medicine & Dentistry, London.
